                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4016: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sackett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-20T23:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 20, 1931—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 20—10:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. Received your No. 81, June 20, 11 a.m. I at once saw the Chancellor and Under
                    Secretary von Billow after our Department conversation. The nature of the
                    desired communication is entirely understood.</p>
                <p>It has had to be prepared under pressure as Von Hindenburg is in East Prussia.
                    You will, I believe, find the draft, which I have seen, satisfactory.</p>
                <p>By midnight I expect to receive the final text and to begin encoding it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sackett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
